's%20a%20notable%20capitulation%20from%20Musk%2C%20who%20viewed%20the%20battle%20as%20an%20ideological%20one%20over%20free%20speech.%20Since%20purchasing%20Twitter%20in%202022%20and%20then%20rebranding%20it%2C%20Musk%20has%20fashioned%20himself%20as%20a%20free%20speech%20absolutist.%20He%20fired%20most%20of%20Twitter's%20trust%20and%20safety%20team%20and%20has%20fought%20authorities%20in%20several%20countries%20over%20efforts%20to%20enforce%20content%20moderation%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20he%20ended%20up%20in%20a%20monthlong%20and%20expensive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-brazil-x-ban-feud-content-moderation-free-speech-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efight%20with%20Brazil's%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20court%20originally%20asked%20X%20to%20remove%20accounts%20associated%20with%20extremist%20groups%20engaging%20in%20disinformation%20campaigns%20favoring%20Jair%20Bolsonaro%2C%20Brazil's%20ousted%20far-right%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20during%20the%20back-and-forth%2C%20Musk%20said%20in%20an%20X%20post%20that%20he%20was%20lifting%20the%20restrictions%20because%20%26quot%3Bprinciples%20matter%20more%20than%20profit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20posted%20to%20X%20a%20dozen%20times%20on%20Saturday%20morning%2C%20but%20did%20not%20address%20the%20news%20out%20of%20Brazil.%20The%20nationwide%20ban%2C%20however%2C%20was%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20X's%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20X%20users%20have%20been%20migrating%20en%20masse%20to%20some%20of%20X's%20biggest%20competitors%2C%20like%20Meta's%20Threads.%20The%20ban%20was%20also%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20company's%20essential%20ad%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20also%20the%20matter%20of%20the%20millions%20in%20fines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20X%20initially%20agreed%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20court's%20orders%2C%20it%20later%20ignored%20them%2C%20so%20Brazilian%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Alexandr