5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-affordability-home-shortage-market-construction-population-cities-zillow-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20housing%20construction%20to%20meet%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20financing%20is%20still%20tight%20for%20home%20builders%2C%20stifling%20momentum%20to%20bring%20more%20housing%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Home%20Builders%2C%20manufacturing%20loans%20climbed%20from%20near%205%25%20lows%20to%2013%25%20since%20March%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20immediate%20effect%20for%20housing%20from%20the%20rate%20cut%20is%20going%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20builder%20and%20the%20land%20developer%20loan%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Danushka%20Nanayakkara-Skillington%2C%20NAHB's%20associate%20vice%20president%20of%20forecasting%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20this%20translates%20into%20a%20much-needed%20supply%20boost%20is%20a%20different%20story%2C%20and%20there%20are%20factors%20the%20Fed%20cut%20won't%20fix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELingering%20uncertainties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Nanayakkara-Skillington%20noted%20that%20material%20pricing%2C%20from%20drywall%20to%20steel%20mill%20products%2C%20has%20weighed%20heavily%20on%20homebuilders%20since%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Flumber-prices-plunge-home-building-season-demand-falls-flat-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elumber%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20normalized%2C%20she%20expects%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nahb.org%2Fblog%2F2024%2F08%2Fcanadian-lumber-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20tariff%20hike%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Canadian%20wood%20to%20increase%20prices%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20on%20Chinese%20transformers%20%E2%80%94%20which%20NAHB%20considers%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nahb.org%2Fadvocacy%2Ftop-priorities%2Fmaterial-costs%2Ftransformers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esorely%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20needed%20component%20delaying%20housing%20projects%20%E2%80%94%20have%20caused%20prices%20to%20jump%2073%25%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20shortages%20to%20consider.%20Nanayakkara-Skillington%20cited%20that%2057%25%20of%20surveyed%20homebuilders%20say%20there%20are%20not%20enough%20lots%20to%20build%20on%2C%20adding%20pricing%20pressure%20to%20the%20available%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUrban%20Institute%20senior%20fellow%20Michael%20Neal%20told%20BI%20that%20local%20regulation%20is%20needed%20to%20remedy%20this%20issue.%20Zoning%20challenges%20should%20be%20addressed%20to%20unleash%20lot%20availability%2C%20he%20said%2C%20while%20inspection%20costs%20and%20timelines%20should%20be%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20issue%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20skilled%20workers%2C%20Nanayakkara-Skillington%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20we%20lost%20about%20a%20million%20construction%20workers%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20we%20still%20lack%20that.%20So%20we%20need%20people%20desperately%20to%20come%20into%20the%20trades%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20citing%20that%20there%20are%20about%20250%2C000%20open%20jobs%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20Fed%20cuts%20should%20improve%20homebuilder%20sentiment%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20after%20a%20period%20of%20declines%20amid%20high%20borrowing%20costs%2C%20both%20analysts%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDim%20views%20on%20existing%20homes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20difficult%20to%20forecast%20when%20the%20housing%20market%20will%20come%20back%20into%20balance%2C%20much%20depends%20on%20whether%20lower%20rates%20entice%20homeowners%20to%20start%20selling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Fitch%20Ratings%2C%20that's%20unlike