uot%3BShe's%20getting%20a%20chance%20to%20write%20her%20own%20story%20there%20and%20at%20least%20has%20been%20able%20to%20somewhat%20drive%20a%20more%20positive%20message%20about%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Kristen%20Soltis%20Anderson%2C%20a%20founding%20partner%20at%20Echelon%20Insights%2C%20said%20on%20a%20press%20call%20hosted%20by%20AARP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoltis%20Anderson%20discussed%20a%20poll%20that%20the%20interest%20group%20commissioned%2C%20which%20found%20Harris%20has%20expanded%20Biden's%20once-meager%20lead%20over%20women%20voters%20aged%2050%20and%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20FiveThirtyEight's%20polling%20average%2C%20Americans%20now%20have%20slightly%20more%20favorable%20views%20of%20Harris%20than%20unfavorable.%20This%20is%20a%20dramatic%20shift%2C%20considering%20Harris%20was%20once%20polling%20so%20low%20that%2C%20at%20times%2C%20she%20flirted%20with%20being%20the%20least%20popular%20vice%20president%20in%20recent%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20shine%20a%20bit%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20do%20when%20you're%20the%20No.%202.%20By%20definition%2C%20a%20large%20part%20of%20your%20job%20is%20to%20stand%20a%20few%20feet%20to%20the%20left%20and%20a%20few%20feet%20behind%20the%20president%20and%20be%20supportive%2C%26quot%3B%20Debbie%20Walsh%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20American%20Women%20and%20Politics%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAs%20opposed%20to%20now%20being%20the%20person%20who%20is%20front%20and%20center%20and%20is%20allowed%20to%20talk%20about%20who%20she%20is%2C%20what%20she%20wants%20to%20accomplish%2C%20and%20she%20is%20allowed%20to%20talk%20about%20her%20strengths%20and%20what%20she%20brings%20to%20the%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Malloy%2C%20a%20polling%20analyst%20for%20the%20Quinnipiac%20University%20Poll%2C%20said%20that%20favorability%20is%20a%20massive%20umbrella%20encompassing%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20emotions%20voters%20have%20for%20candidates.%20Likability%20also%20has%20a%20fraught%20history%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20female%20candidates%2C%20as%20best%20encapsulated%20by%20Barack%20Obama's%20infamous%202008%20jab%20that%20his%20Democratic%20senate%20colleague%20Hillary%20Clinton%20was%20%26quot%3Blikable%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris'%20reversal%20of%20fortunes%20is%20a%20warning%20sign%20for%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20campaign.%20Despite%20his%20and%20his%20allies'%20best%20efforts%2C%20voters%20have%20yet%20to%20buy%20into%20their%20branding%20of%20Harris%20as%20a%20progressive%20chameleon%20who%20can't%20be%20trusted.%20Even%20top%20Republicans%2C%20including%20former%20UN%20ambassador%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20have%20recoiled%20at%20Trump's%20attacks%2C%20including%20questioning%20her%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20shaken%20up%20an%20election%20that%20once%20seemed%20poised%20to%20feature%20two%20of%20the%20least%20popular%20major%20presidential%20candidates%20since%201980%2C%20as%20FiveThirtyEight%20documented%20earlier%20this%20spring.%20Her%20rise%20is%20all%20the%20more%20remarkable%20given%20the%20hyperpartisanship%20that%20has%20overshadowed%20US%20politics%20to%20the%20point%20that%20some%20even%20wondered%20if%20there%20would%20ever%20be%20a%20return%20of%20popular%20presidential%20hopefuls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Gabe%20Fleisher%20wrote%20in%20his%20newsletter%2C%20Wake%20Up%20To%20Politics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wakeuptopolitics.com%2Fp%2Fkamala-harris-has-done-something%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20explanation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20shift%20could%20be%20very%20simple.%20Research%20shows%20Americans%20don't%20form%20strong%20opinions%20of%20vice%20presidents.%20Now%2C%20reexamined%20on%20her%20terms%2C%20Harris%20has%2C%20to%20borrow%20one%20of%20her%20lines%2C%20%26quot%3Bunburdened%20by%20what%20has%20been.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20could%20still%20win%20this%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris'%20campaign%20still%20views%20itself%20as%20an%20underdog.%20Famed%20forecaster%20Nate%20Silver's%20model%20has%20returned%20to%20essentially%20a%20coin%20flip%2C%20though%20on%20Friday%2C%20it%20showed%20Harris%20with%20the%20first%20edge%20in%20weeks%20in%20the%20race%20to%20win%20the%20electoral%20college.%20The%20former%20president%20has%20been%20here%20before.%20Despite%20the%20reality%20that%20the%20most%20favorable%20candidate%20usually%20wins%2C%20he%20emerged%20victorious%20over%20Hillary%20Clinton%20in%202016%20(who%20was%20also%20unpopular%2C%20though%20not%20nearly%20as%20disliked%20as%20he%20was).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%202016%2C%20though.%20Walsh%20said%20Clinton's%20failure%20was%20a%20flash%20point%20for%20women%20in%20American%20politics%2C%20a%20trend%20she%20thinks%20will%20benefit%20Harris.%20More%20women%20are%20now%20running%20for%20office%20and%20getting%20involved%20in%20politics%20than%20ever%20before.%20There's%20now%20a%20larger%20percentage%20of%20women%20in%20Congress%20than%20at%20any%20other%20point%20in%20American%20history%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Clinton%2C%20Walsh%20pointed%20out%20Harris%20hasn't%20spent%20decades%20in%20the%20spotlight%20and%20isn't%20faced%20with%20assuaging%20voters'%20fears%20of%20a%20potential%20political%20dynasty.%20Clinton's%20favorability%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20took%20almost%20the%20complete%20opposite%20journey%20from%20Harris'.%20Clinton%20was%20viewed%20more%20favorably%20as%20President%20Obama's%20Secretary%20of%20State.%20Still%2C%20that%20goodwill%20dissipated%20as%20she%20geared%20up%20to%20become%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20be%20a%20major%20party's%20presidential%20nominee%20and%20was%20made%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bcaricature%20of%20who%20she%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20Walsh's%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20you%20remember%2C%20but%20you%20could%20buy%20in%20airports%20the%20'Hillary%20Clinton'%20nutcracker%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Walsh%2C%20whose%20center%20is%20based%20at%20Rutgers%20University.%20%26quot%3BIt%20played%20out%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20gender-based%2C%20but%20compounded%20by%20all%20of%20these%20other%20factors%20that%20went%20into%20her%20candidacy%20and%20the%20public's%20reaction%20to%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22393ea36a-abb6-444c-bf74-6b2fa33cdd47%5C%22%3EThis%20isn't%20Trump's%20only%20struggle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Trump's%20allies%2C%20North%20Carolina%20Lt.%20Gov.%20Mark%20Robinson%2C%20is%20pressing%20on%20with%20a%20struggling%20gubernatorial%20campaign%20in%20a%20state%20that%20Democrats%20have%20only%20carried%20once%20this%20century%20(2008)%20but%20is%20now%20too%20close%20to%20call%20amid%20Harris'%20rise.%20Robinson%20is%20trying%20to%20press%20through%20the%20latest%20scandal%20that%20he%20called%20himself%20a%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Nazi%26quot%3B%20on%20a%20pornography%20forum%20decades%20ago.%20(Robinson%20has%20denied%20those%20are%20his%20words%2C%20despite%20CNN%20obtaining%20voluminous%20evidence%20to%20the%20contrary.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20running%20mate%2C%20Sen.%20JD%20Vance%2C%20remains%20deeply%20unpopular.%20And%20by%20almost%20every%20account%2C%20Trump%20lost%20the%20first%20and%20perhaps%20only%20debate%20to%20Harris.%20Democrats%20are%20even%20cutting%20into%20Trump's%20advantage%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20campaign's%20biggest%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20news%20he%20received%20all%20week%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flindsey-graham-trump-electoral-college-nebraska-tweak-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublicans%20in%20Nebraska%20%3C%2Fa%3Emay%20try%20one%20final%20time%20to%20change%20the%20state's%20laws%20to%20deprive%20Harris%20of%20a%20likely%20Electoral%20College%20vote%2C%20potentially%20eroding%20her%20Great%20Lakes%20states%2F%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbattleground-states-2024-p