nic%20risk%2C%20we%20also%20identified%20non-carcinogenic%20health%20risks%20posed%20by%20chromium%20in%20the%20groundwater%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20heavy%20metals%2C%20her%20study%20also%20investigated%20the%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20exposure%20in%20the%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hazard%20quotient%20analysis%20revealed%20that%20the%20oral%20pathway%2C%20i.e.%20drinking%20contaminated%20water%2C%20was%20the%20primary%20route%20of%20exposure%20for%20all%20age%20groups.%20Fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20were%20found%20to%20be%20the%20major%20contributors%20to%20these%20health%20risks%20with%20children%20and%20infants%20being%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20their%20effects.%20Fluoride%2C%20when%20consumed%20in%20excess%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20dental%20and%20skeletal%20fluorosis%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20discolouration%20and%20damage%20to%20the%20teeth%20and%20bones.%20Nitrate%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20interfere%20with%20the%20blood%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20carry%20oxygen%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20condition%20called%20methemoglobinemia%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20dangerous%20for%20infants%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EImpact%20of%20climate%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%2027%20July%20to%2030%20July%202024%2C%20around%2012%20flights%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20touch%20down%20at%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F139355%2Fbakula-rinpoche-ladakhi-monastery-democracy-mongolia-sushma-swaraj%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKushok%20Bakula%20Rinpoche%3C%2Fa%3E%20Airport%20while%20many%20more%20were%20cancelled.%20The%20maximum%20operating%20temperature%20of%20Leh%20airport%20is%2032%C2%B0C%20but%20on%2028%20July%2C%20the%20Leh%20division%20recorded%2033.5%C2%B0C%20as%20per%20the%20Metrology%20Centre%20of%20Ladakh.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20temperature%20recorded%20in%20the%20Kargil%20division%20was%2037.5%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELadakh%20was%20burning%20this%20summer%20because%20of%20a%20huge%20deficit%20in%20rainfall.%20It%20received%203%20mm%20of%20rainfall%20till%20the%20start%20of%20August%20as%20against%20the%20normal%20of%2015%20mm.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lack%20of%20precipitation%20and%20intense%20heat%20wave%20has%20dried%20out%20the%20soil%2C%20causing%20crops%20to%20wither%20and%20trees%20to%20require%20more%20water.%20Meanwhile%2C%20groundwater%20exploitation%20by%20drilling%20more%20borewells%20has%20further%20accelerated%20the%20decline%20in%20groundwater%20levels%20and%20reserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20all%20know%2C%20Leh%20is%20located%20in%20a%20high-altitude%20desert%20region%2C%20where%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20water%20for%20our%20aquifers%20is%20the%20melting%20of%20glaciers%20and%20snowpack%20in%20the%20surrounding%20mountains.%20However%2C%20as%20recent%20events%20indicate%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20causing%20significant%20alterations%20to%20this%20delicate%20balance%2C%20leading%20to%20severe%20consequences%20for%20our%20groundwater%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Overview%20of%20Leh%20Town%3A%20Climate%20change%20is%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20region's%20groundwater%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2